Introduction

Kim Jong Woon, popularly known as Yesung, is a South Korean singer and actor. Yesung rose to fame for being the main vocalist of the legendary boy group Super Junior under SM Entertainment.

Yesung made his first television appearance in 1999 and became a trainee under SM Entertainment when he auditioned for "Starlight Casting System 2001". He eventually made his official debut on November 6, 2005.
